<!-- Step-by-Step On-Page SEO Checklist -->
<section style="padding:50px 20px;max-width:900px;margin:auto;">

<h2>Step 1: Keyword Optimization</h2>
<p>Every page should target a primary keyword, supported by secondary and long-tail keywords. For example:</p>
<ul>
<li>Primary: “on-page SEO checklist”</li>
<li>Secondary: “SEO optimization tips for beginners”</li>
<li>Long-tail: “how to optimize website pages for SEO in Kenya”</li>
</ul>
<p>Use these keywords in your:</p>
<ul>
<li>Title and headings</li>
<li>First paragraph of your content</li>
<li>Meta description</li>
<li>Internal anchor links</li>
</ul>

<h2>Step 2: Title Tag Optimization</h2>
<p>Titles must be clear, clickable, and include your target keywords. Keep under 60 characters.</p>
<p>Example: <strong>“On-Page SEO Checklist for Beginners (2026 Guide)”</strong></p>

<h2>Step 3: Meta Description</h2>
<p>Meta descriptions improve click-through rate. Include main keywords, make it engaging, and stay under 160 characters.</p>

<h2>Step 4: Header Tags (H1, H2, H3)</h2>
<p>Organize your content with headings for readability and SEO. Use H1 for the main title, H2 for sections, and H3 for subsections.</p>

<h2>Step 5: Content Quality & Search Intent</h2>
<p>Your content must solve problems, answer questions, and match search intent. This keeps visitors longer and improves rankings.</p>
<p>Related reading: <a href="/blog/why-website-not-ranking-google-2026.html" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">Why your website is not ranking on Google</a></p>

<h2>Step 6: Internal Linking</h2>
<p>Internal links help Google crawl your site and guide users. Always link to:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#services" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">SEO services</a></li>
<li><a href="#portfolio" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">case studies</a></li>
<li><a href="#contact" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">contact section</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>Step 7: Image Optimization</h2>
<p>Use descriptive filenames, add alt text, and compress images for faster loading.</p>

<h2>Step 8: URL Structure</h2>
<p>Keep URLs short, keyword-rich, and readable. Example: <strong>/blog/on-page-seo-checklist-2026.html</strong></p>

<h2>Step 9: Page Speed Optimization</h2>
<p>Optimize loading by compressing images, reducing code, and enabling caching.</p>

<h2>Step 10: Mobile Optimization</h2>
<p>Ensure your website is responsive, loads fast, and is easy to navigate on smartphones.</p>

